DROP and TRUNCATE commands are the DDL commands which are used to delete tables from the database and once the table gets deleted, all the privileges and indexes that are related to the table also get deleted. These 2 operations cannot be rolled back and so should be used only when necessary. DELETE command, on the other hand, is a DML Command which is also used to delete rows from the table and this can be rolled back.
